    {
      "area": "DeliveryStatusChanged event schema",
      "reason": "This is the contract between the Delivery and Notification bounded contexts. Changes to this schema require coordination. Use schema versioning from day one (include a 'version' field). This rigidity is intentional — stable contracts between contexts are a feature, not a bug."
    },
    {
      "area": "At-least-once delivery semantics",
      "reason": "The system is built around at-least-once delivery, which requires idempotent workers. This is a foundational assumption — switching to exactly-once would require significant rework. Lock this in as a design principle."
    },
    {
      "area": "Queue infrastructure choice",
      "reason": "Switching from SQS to Pub/Sub (or vice versa) requires changing queue client code in every component. Mitigate with a thin queue abstraction layer if multi-cloud is a future possibility, but don't over-abstract for a 3-person team."
    }
  ],

