    "patterns_to_follow": "1. Keep the Delivery Service completely ignorant of notifications — it publishes events, period. 2. Each Channel Worker must be idempotent — duplicate messages must not cause duplicate sends. 3. Use a base worker class to standardize retry counting, error logging, and DLQ escalation across channels. 4. Schema-version your domain events from day one. 5. One queue per channel for failure isolation. 6. Monitor DLQ depth — this is your reliability guarantee.",
