      "Do NOT skip idempotency — at-least-once delivery WILL cause duplicates in production. Customers receiving 3 identical SMS messages erodes trust",
      "Do NOT put notification template rendering in the Router — keep it in Channel Workers so each channel can format independently",
      "Do NOT create a shared 'notification' queue for all channels — one slow provider will create head-of-line blocking for all channels"
    ]
  },

  "escalations": [],

  "confidence": {
    "level": 92,
    "high_confidence_areas": [
      "Option B is superior to Option A given the stated constraints — the 5-minute latency tolerance, reliability requirement, and extensibility need all point unambiguously to event-driven",
      "Managed queue over self-hosted broker for a 3-person team",
      "Per-channel queue isolation for failure containment",
      "Idempotency requirement for at-least-once semantics"
    ],
    "low_confidence_areas": [
      "Specific queue technology choice (SQS vs pg-boss) depends on existing infrastructure which was not specified",
      "Customer preference storage model depends on existing database and data architecture",
